         <abstract id="aspace_f5364b0ffe7ebcbff82949d7425ee15f">The papers include correspondence mainly regarding Astle's work in the Record Office. There is also correspondence with James Adams about his work on grammar, with Charles Blagden about the Pompeiian excavations, and with Harriot Collinson about her husband's work (John Collinson's "The History and Antiquities of the County of Somerset"). Much of the correspondence is annotated in an unidentified hand.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no90021007"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Astle, Thomas, 1735-1803</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
